HEADWORD: Motty
<hw>Mot"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of, or consisting
of, motes.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>mottie</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>motty</qex> dust reek raised by the workmen.</q>
<rj><qau>H. Miller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

